modules.description: This module provides low-level byte sequence manipulation, memory operations, and binary data handling through direct indexing, slicing, and in-place modification. It operates on mutable bigstrings—fixed-length byte arrays—with support for endianness-aware integer encoding, memory-mapped regions, and character-based traversal. Key use cases include binary protocol implementation, memory-efficient data processing, and systems programming tasks requiring precise control over byte-level representations.
